Ask HN: Infringing Patents as a Solopreneur
text:
I'm currently developing a web app and had a thought last night that one of the pieces of functionality I created might be novel enough to be granted a patent.

This led me to searching https://ppubs.uspto.gov/pubwebapp/ and finding https://patents.google.com/ where I think I discovered there are existing active patents at Big Tech company(s) around the area that I'm working in.

How much should I be concerned about potentially infringing on others patents? Does anyone have any experience / war stories of how things might play out?

I realise being sued for patent infringement is one of those "good problems to have", but it is something in the back of my mind (especially knowing that patent trolls have come after some of the larger companies in my space).

Ask HN: Is Slack ending their Fair Billing policy?
text: I am hearing from multiple sources that Slack is telling Enterprise customers the Fair Billing policy will end at the customer's next renewal. However, even though this seems like a major change for Slack, there is no mention of this anywhere public that I can see. I would be interested in hearing if anyone on HN can confirm this rumor.

Ask HN: Will toroidal propellers change the world?
text:
I was watching YouTube videos about the efficiency gains from toroidal propellers, which have been developed at MIT.

I wondered to what extent these are likely to change the world, given that propeller efficiency has a gigantic impact on so many aspects of society.

Anyone here with the expertise to know possible futures for toroidal propeller innovation?
